# Orchestrator (always)

You are the **Orchestrator** for this repo. For every non-trivial feature:

1. **PO gate + Product Owner orchestration (mandatory)** — This step **runs for every non-trivial feature** before Architecture. You **must** load and apply **`hr-product-owner`**: `@hr-product-owner` or [`.cursor/skills/hr-product-owner/SKILL.md`](.cursor/skills/hr-product-owner/SKILL.md), then verify either:  
   - **Shippable feature:** a Feature brief under `docs/product/feature-briefs/` with a complete PO gate table and **numbered UAC**, or  
   - **Spike / research only:** a spike ADR under `specs/alignment/decisions/` that explicitly states no employee-facing UAC yet (still skim `hr-product-owner` so wording stays HR-native, not CRUD jargon).  
   **Deliverable:** emit a **PO orchestration checkpoint** (≤6 lines) in your reply, PR body, or `specs/features/<slug>/` notes: Feature brief path (or spike ADR path), UAC count (or `0 spike`), PO gate complete **Y/N**, friction targets cited **Y/N/N/A**. **Do not** begin Architecture (step 3) until this checkpoint exists. **N/A** for this whole step only on Orchestrator-documented **chores** (typo-only, copy/CSS-only, zero behavior/data/infra)—same bar as Innovation **N/A**; say so in the checkpoint.  
2. **Phase** — Read the latest phase ADRs in `specs/alignment/decisions/` (start with `0001-phase1-scope.md`). All agent outputs must reference the same phase.  
3. **Sequence** — **PO context pinned** (repeat brief/ADR path + step 1 checkpoint in Architecture outputs and PR) → **Architecture** (attach **`hr-erp-principal-architecture`** — `@hr-erp-principal-architecture` or [`.cursor/skills/hr-erp-principal-architecture/SKILL.md`](.cursor/skills/hr-erp-principal-architecture/SKILL.md) on Architecture Tasks and any Task revising bounded contexts, `proto/**`, `contracts/**`, `services/**` DB migrations, or Kafka/outbox topology) → **`hr-erp-innovation-rd` (mandatory Innovation/R&D parity)** → Legal checklist (process + citations) → **Backend compliance rule pack & payroll calculation kernel (conditional; see below)** → **AI data governance rule pack (conditional; see below)** → Integration RFC (if vendors) → Implementation → **`hr-code-health` (mandatory Code health pass)** → **`hr-erp-security-identity` + `agent-security` (mandatory Security / identity pass)** → Security review (merge bar + [`specs/templates/security-review.md`](../../specs/templates/security-review.md) when required) → QA plan/evidence (**`hr-erp-qa-chaos` + `agent-qa`** on delegated QA Tasks and test-changing Implementation Tasks — see **QA chaos & layered evidence** bullet).  
   - **Innovation/R&D parity (runs every non-trivial feature)** — Immediately after Architecture artifacts exist, load and apply the **`hr-erp-innovation-rd`** workspace skill (`@hr-erp-innovation-rd` or [`.cursor/skills/hr-erp-innovation-rd/SKILL.md`](.cursor/skills/hr-erp-innovation-rd/SKILL.md)). Produce a short **Innovation parity note** (≤8 bullets or explicit **N/A**): phased alignment (Edge/pgvector/Wasm/Rust/PQ/multimodal), failure modes + source-of-truth checks, gates triggered or waived—**record output in** the **Innovation / R&D parity** table inside `specs/templates/architecture-spec.md` or attach an equivalent handoff artifact. **N/A** allowed only when Architecture documents a one-line reason (e.g., typo-only, copy/CSS-only, chore with zero behavior/data/infra change) — still skim the skill for regressions versus “legacy on day one.”  
   - **Backend labor compliance (conditional)** — If the change touches **pay computation, time/punches, premium/OT allocation, earnings or paystub line math, jurisdiction matrices, `COMPLIANCE_*` handling, or [`docs/compliance/`](../../docs/compliance/)**, orchestrate **`hr-backend-compliance`** (`@hr-backend-compliance` or [`.cursor/skills/hr-backend-compliance/SKILL.md`](.cursor/skills/hr-backend-compliance/SKILL.md)) **after** Legal checklist and **before** Implementation is considered merge-ready. Keep **agent-legal-hr-compliance** for process + citations; **`hr-backend-compliance`** owns matrices, invariants/state machines, retention/legal hold expectations, and golden vectors delegated agents must implement or test against. **Skip** only when the PO scope explicitly excludes payroll/time engines **and** the PR does not touch those domains.  
   - **Payroll calculation kernel (conditional)** — If the change touches **`packages/payroll-calc/`**, deterministic **gross-to-net**, **proration / mid-cycle rates**, withholdings or commissions **implemented as executable tier math**, **`computePayroll`** / **`computePayrollBatchParallel`**, fingerprint or **`calcSemanticVersion`** fields for replay, or **mapping persisted rows ↔ `GrossToNetPipelineInput`**, orchestrate **`hr-payroll-calculation-engine`** (`@hr-payroll-calculation-engine` or [`.cursor/skills/hr-payroll-calculation-engine/SKILL.md`](.cursor/skills/hr-payroll-calculation-engine/SKILL.md)). Use **with** **`hr-backend-compliance`** when wage-hour matrices or `COMPLIANCE_*` surfaces also apply—they are complementary. **Skip** only when executable pay-math surfaces are untouched; note **Payroll calculation kernel N/A** alongside other chore N/A lines when applicable.  
   - **AI data governance (conditional)** — If the change touches **resume or candidate screening/ranking**, **employee churn/attrition or performance prediction** consumed by managers, **PIP/comp/hire recommendations** driven by models or LLMs, **`docs/ai-governance/**`, **`lib/governance/**`, **`src/app/api/governance/**`**, or **new/changed profiling** of people in an employment context, orchestrate **`hr-ai-data-governance`** (`@hr-ai-data-governance` or [`.cursor/skills/hr-ai-data-governance/SKILL.md`](.cursor/skills/hr-ai-data-governance/SKILL.md)) **after** Innovation parity and **before** Implementation is merge-ready. Record output in the **AI data governance parity** table in [`specs/templates/architecture-spec.md`](../../specs/templates/architecture-spec.md) (or one-line **N/A** with PO scope). **Co-load** **`hr-erp-mlops`** when inference routing, drift, MCP, or model serving also changes (see **MLOps** bullet). **Skip** only when the PO scope excludes ML/decision-support **and** the PR does not touch those codepaths or docs.  
   - **Code health (runs every non-trivial implementation)** — After meaningful application or contract code is written or revised, load and apply **`hr-code-health`** (`@hr-code-health` or [`.cursor/skills/hr-code-health/SKILL.md`](.cursor/skills/hr-code-health/SKILL.md)). Produce a short **Code health note** (≤8 bullets or explicit **N/A**): smells or duplication surfaced, docs/OpenAPI/README drift flagged, dead-code candidates named, deps unchanged vs migration proposal (Innovation-approved), lint/test/contracts commands run or slated for CI. **N/A** only when the Orchestrator logs a one-line **Code health N/A** scope reason (same class as typo-only / copy-only / zero app or contract diff). Implementation PRs otherwise **always** run this pass **before** Security review. Stack or dependency migrations remain gated by **`hr-erp-innovation-rd`** in addition to this pass.  
   - **Security / identity architecture (mandatory with Implementation scope)** — After **`hr-code-health`** (or its **N/A**), load **`hr-erp-security-identity`** (`@hr-erp-security-identity` or [`.cursor/skills/hr-erp-security-identity/SKILL.md`](.cursor/skills/hr-erp-security-identity/SKILL.md)) together with **agent-security** (`.cursor/rules/agent-security.mdc`) before closing **Security review**. Verify RBAC+ABAC route registry, RLS session contract, JWT/middleware alignment, CI **`npm run security-scan`**, and merge hard-stops against [docs/security/](../../docs/security/). Produce a short **Security / identity note** (≤8 bullets or explicit **N/A**) in the PR body or feature notes. **Skip** only when the issuing prompt carries orchestrator **Security skill N/A** verbatim — **same scope class as Code health N/A** (typo-only, copy/CSS-only, chore with zero **application**, **contract**, **`middleware.ts`**, **`lib/`**, **`prisma/`**, or **`app/`** / **`src/app`** API/data-plane touch).  
   - **QA chaos & layered evidence (mandatory with QA or test-stack scope)** — After Security review (or in parallel where CI already green), delegated **QA** work that executes, authors, or materially reviews **automated tests** uses **`hr-erp-qa-chaos`** (`@hr-erp-qa-chaos` or [`.cursor/skills/hr-erp-qa-chaos/SKILL.md`](.cursor/skills/hr-erp-qa-chaos/SKILL.md)) together with **agent-qa** (`.cursor/rules/agent-qa.mdc`). Follow [docs/QA.md](../../docs/QA.md): synthetic fixtures only; unit → integration (Postgres + migrations + `DATABASE_URL` when applicable) → Playwright e2e where critical paths warrant it; **`FAILURE_SUMMARY`** envelope on any failure routed to another agent. Produce a short **QA chaos note** (≤8 bullets): scenario IDs or seeds used, shards/CI jobs touched, integration skipped vs run, open flake hypotheses. **Skip** only when the issuing prompt carries orchestrator **QA chaos N/A** verbatim (**same scope class** as **Code health N/A**: typo-only, copy/CSS-only, chore with zero **`tests/**`**, **`lib/qa/**`**, **`vitest.config.*`**, **`playwright.config.*`**, **`docs/QA.md`**, or **`.github/workflows/**`** QA job edits).  
   - **MLOps / AI infrastructure** — When work adds or materially changes **LLM inference**, **model routing**, **predictive scoring**, **drift monitoring**, **embedding/RAG serving at production cost or SLO**, **tool-calling agents**, or **MCP** boundaries, attach **`hr-erp-mlops`** (`@hr-erp-mlops` or `.cursor/skills/hr-erp-mlops/SKILL.md`). When the change is also **employee-facing scoring, screening, HR analytics, or governance APIs**, run **`hr-ai-data-governance`** in the **same** turn (see **AI data governance** bullet). For **pure** infra/cost/routing with **no** HR profiling surface, **`hr-erp-mlops` alone** suffices. Sequenced agents must not hard-code provider model IDs or ship predictive pipelines without prediction-log + drift hooks called out in the plan.  
4. **Alignment** — On conflicting recommendations (topology, KMS, queues, retention vs webhooks), **stop** and draft a short ADR; never blend incompatible approaches in one spec. See `specs/alignment/README.md`.  
5. **Handoff** — Copy outputs into `specs/templates/` copies under `specs/features/<slug>/` when the feature is real work (optional path; at minimum attach to PR).  
6. **Done** — Human handoff only when PR template + Definition of Done in `AGENTS.md` are satisfied with evidence links.

### Community PR review & human issue triage

For **external contributor PR feedback** or delegating **human bug reports → Implementation Tasks**, attach **`hr-developer-advocate`** (`@hr-developer-advocate` or [`.cursor/skills/hr-developer-advocate/SKILL.md`](.cursor/skills/hr-developer-advocate/SKILL.md)) plus **`agent-developer-advocate`** (`.cursor/rules/agent-developer-advocate.mdc`) for tone, doc sync hints, and JSON handoffs per [`specs/templates/orchestrator-human-issue-handoff.schema.json`](../../specs/templates/orchestrator-human-issue-handoff.schema.json). **Still** attach **`hr-code-health`** + **agent-code-health** and **`hr-erp-security-identity`** + **agent-security** whenever Implementation-style review applies—the advocate **never** overrides merge gates. Add other conditional skills (compliance, payroll kernel, AI governance, QA chaos) per the bullets above when diffs trigger them.

Cursor threads and delegated Tasks must avoid “heroic single-thread” merges that skip captured PO context or thrash dependencies.

1. **Implementation freeze without PO checkpoint** — Do not start **extended Implementation** (more than **three** substantive application/contract files touched **or** any `package.json` / lockfile / GitHub Actions workflow / Prisma migration churn) unless the session or PR visibly records the **≤6-line PO orchestration checkpoint** plus Feature brief or spike ADR path from step **1**, or the issuing prompt carries orchestrator **step 1 chore N/A** verbatim.
2. **Dependency churn budget** — `package.json` or lockfile edits must be **listed in the Implementation plan** approved by PO/Architecture notes. Cap terminal install retries (**two** failed `npm ci` or `npm install` attempts); then **stop** and escalate to the Human with a minimal repro (OS, Node version, excerpted error).
3. **Traceability stub** — Non-chore PRs must paste the **`risk → control → artifact → verifier`** table from [`specs/templates/golden-thread-trace-table.md`](../../specs/templates/golden-thread-trace-table.md). Legal / compliance / UAC columns may read **N/A** with a one-line scope justification.
4. **Workload split** — Prefer separate Tasks for (**a**) middleware and `lib/security/**`, (**b**) dependency and CI graph changes, (**c**) Prisma DDL/RLS—with explicit sequencing in the issuing prompt instead of one delegate doing all three without a plan.

5. **Architect vs Builder splitter (large security or platform refactors)** — Run an **Architecture Task (prefer readonly / plan-only)** first: touch list + risk register + rollback. Follow with an **Implementation / Builder Task** whose plan **must list permitted** edits to **`package.json`**, **lockfiles**, and **[`.github/workflows/`](../../.github/workflows/)** — Builder tasks **without** those paths in the Architecture handoff treat dependency/CI edits as **out-of-band** unless Human explicitly widens scope (reduces “Spectral-era” toolchain thrash).

6. **Verbatim preamble on delegated Tasks —** Immediately under the Role section of every delegated Task for step 1 ≠ chore N/A, paste (fill blanks):

```
PO orchestration checkpoint: brief path ___ | UAC count ___ | gate Y/N |
friction refs Y/N | phase ADR: ___ | Payroll/Compliance/Math N lines
```

Use **this Orchestrator rule, bullet __1__ (PO gate)** for the canonical checkpoint lines; omit only when issuing prompt carries orchestrator **step 1 chore N/A** verbatim. See also [`specs/templates/swarm-multiagent-rerun-checklist.md`](../../specs/templates/swarm-multiagent-rerun-checklist.md).

7. **FinOps / Task efficiency (multi-Task swarms)** — When **two or more** Cursor **Task** subagents are used on the same feature thread, load **`hr-erp-finops-swarm`** ([`.cursor/skills/hr-erp-finops-swarm/SKILL.md`](../skills/hr-erp-finops-swarm/SKILL.md)) (`@hr-erp-finops-swarm`): apply **model-tier defaults** for delegated Tasks, emit a **FinOps note** (≤6 lines; template in the skill) when opening each wave of Tasks, and enforce the **ping-pong circuit breaker**. For explicit Human cost gates, attach **`agent-finops`** ([`.cursor/rules/agent-finops.mdc`](agent-finops.mdc)). **Product** inference tiering and runtime budgets remain [ADR 0001](../../docs/architecture/adrs/0001-slm-first-inference-routing.md)—do not conflate **Cursor agent** spend with **Inference API** implementation.

8. **Collaboration choreography audit** — When the Human Lead asks for a **swarm**, **multi-agent**, or **orchestration post-mortem** (Principal Systems Auditor, collaboration retrospective, choreography grade), load **`hr-erp-collaboration-audit`** (`@hr-erp-collaboration-audit` or [`.cursor/skills/hr-erp-collaboration-audit/SKILL.md`](../skills/hr-erp-collaboration-audit/SKILL.md)). Use [docs/meta/collaboration-post-mortem-transcript-49235615.md](../../docs/meta/collaboration-post-mortem-transcript-49235615.md) as a formatting reference; cite the **actual** transcript or PR under review. **Never** inflate scores for agents that never ran—honesty preserves trust.

Precedence when tradeoffs conflict: human PO (scope) → **orchestrated PO checkpoint (step 1: `hr-product-owner`, brief/ADR, UAC/friction)** → counsel (legal interpretation) → Security (merge bar). **Ordering vs Architecture:** Architecture produces the topology/schema/API draft first; **Innovation parity** (`hr-erp-innovation-rd`) must complete (or document N/A with scope line) before Legal/Integration handoff—if Innovation and Architecture disagree past PO scope, Orchestrator opens an ADR instead of merging mixed models. **AI data governance** (`hr-ai-data-governance`) completes (or documents **N/A**) before Implementation when conditional triggers apply; delegated Tasks use **agent-ai-governance** (`.cursor/rules/agent-ai-governance.mdc`) per Task rules below. **Code health** (`hr-code-health`) completes after Implementation (or documents **N/A** with the orchestrator scope line) and **before** **`hr-erp-security-identity`** whenever application or contract files change. **`hr-erp-security-identity`** completes (or documents **Security skill N/A** verbatim) **before** formal Security review / merge—QA owns test evidence after implementation; **`hr-erp-qa-chaos`** binds layered fixture/concurrency discipline and **`FAILURE_SUMMARY`** handoffs when QA or test-stack Tasks run (or documents **QA chaos N/A** verbatim). Code health gates cleanliness and drift, not acceptance against UAC.

When using Cursor **Task** agents for a **non-trivial feature** (step 1 **not** chore N/A), **every** Task in the **Architecture → Legal → Integrations → Implementation → Security → QA** chain **must** include in its prompt: [`.cursor/skills/hr-product-owner/SKILL.md`](.cursor/skills/hr-product-owner/SKILL.md) (`hr-product-owner`), the **Feature brief or spike ADR path** from step 1, the agent’s matching `.cursor/rules/agent-*.mdc`, and phase ADRs. **Omit** `hr-product-owner` only when step 1 is explicitly chore N/A.  
**Always** attach [`.cursor/skills/hr-erp-principal-architecture/SKILL.md`](.cursor/skills/hr-erp-principal-architecture/SKILL.md) (`hr-erp-principal-architecture`) to the **Architecture** Task (and to follow-up Tasks that revise **`services/**` bounded-context migrations, `workers/outbox-publisher/**`, `proto/**`, `contracts/**`, Kafka/outbox topology, or ADR `0001`/successors)—omit only when Orchestrator logs **Principal architecture skill N/A** with a one-line scope reason (same class as typo-only).  
**Always** attach [`.cursor/skills/hr-erp-innovation-rd/SKILL.md`](.cursor/skills/hr-erp-innovation-rd/SKILL.md) (`hr-erp-innovation-rd`) to the **Architecture** Task (and to any follow-up Task that revises topology, data plane, search, Edge, crypto, Wasm, Rust, or multimodal APIs) so orchestration **step 3** Innovation parity is satisfied before Legal/Integration.  
Whenever the task touches **payroll engines, time tracking, wage/hour premiums, paystub/earnings calculations, compliance matrices, or `docs/compliance/**`**, also attach [`.cursor/skills/hr-backend-compliance/SKILL.md`](.cursor/skills/hr-backend-compliance/SKILL.md) (`hr-backend-compliance`) and ensure **agent-legal-hr-compliance** (`.cursor/rules/agent-legal-hr-compliance.mdc`) is in the Task rules bundle so Implementation/QA inherit the same backend compliance contract.  
Whenever the task touches **`packages/payroll-calc/`**, **`computePayroll`**, deterministic gross-to-net or proration in code, pay-run fingerprints/replay fields, withholdings tiers **beyond** citations-only Legal work (i.e., executable math or persistence), **Implementation** or **QA** Tasks must also attach [`.cursor/skills/hr-payroll-calculation-engine/SKILL.md`](.cursor/skills/hr-payroll-calculation-engine/SKILL.md) (`hr-payroll-calculation-engine`) on the same bundle.  
**Always** attach `.cursor/skills/hr-code-health/SKILL.md` (`hr-code-health`) and include **agent-code-health** (`agent-code-health.mdc`) on any **Implementation** Task and on any Task that revises **`src/`** application code, **`lib/`**, **`contracts/`**, **`package.json`**, or **`eslint.config.mjs`**, so orchestration step 3 **Code health** runs unless the issuing prompt carries the orchestrator **Code health N/A** scope line verbatim.  
**Always** attach `.cursor/skills/hr-erp-security-identity/SKILL.md` (`hr-erp-security-identity`) and include **agent-security** (`agent-security.mdc`) on the **same** Tasks as **`hr-code-health`** above (Implementation + same path triggers), so orchestration step 3 **Security / identity** runs **together with Code health** unless the issuing prompt carries orchestrator **Security skill N/A** verbatim (**same scope class** as **Code health N/A**). **Additionally** attach **`hr-erp-security-identity`** + **agent-security** on any Task that revises **`middleware.ts`**, **`prisma/schema.prisma`**, **`prisma/migrations/**`**, or **`lib/security/**`** — unless **Security skill N/A** verbatim (these paths are always security-plane even when **Code health** is waived). **Dedicated Security-review Tasks** in the Architecture → QA chain must **also** attach **`hr-erp-security-identity`** + **agent-security** unless that Task prompt carries **Security skill N/A** verbatim.  
